        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 5:05AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 505 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm over
Garfield, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Pea Ridge...                      Garfield...
Gateway...                        Hill Top...
Walnut Hill...                    Busch...
Beaver...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
northwestern Arkansas.</instruction>
